modules.description: This module extracts version information from a Git repository and saves it into an OCaml source file. It provides functions to run `git describe`, optionally handling dirty flags and custom Git directories, and to write the resulting version string as a binding in a specified file. It also includes parsed version data for the OCaml compiler, when available, as a tuple of major, minor, patch, and remaining version components.

This module extracts version information from a Git repository by running `git describe`, supporting optional handling of dirty flags and custom Git directories. It writes the resulting version string as a binding in a specified OCaml source file and includes parsed version data for the OCaml compiler as a tuple of major, minor, patch, and remaining components. Useful for embedding version information directly into compiled OCaml projects during a build process.
